<br>
The issues of late basically have come from feelings coming to a boiling point on our server.  Other than the simple flames that have cropped up, there is a list of specific grievances brought against a certain group of people.  This list includes a number of incidents where the accused group of people acted in ways that brought general bad-feeling and unrest to others on our server.  The discussion (and ensuing flames to a point) were directed at rectifying the behavior of the accused group of people.<br>
<br>
The two points<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
- When you point your finger at me, three of them are pointing back at you.<br>
- The pot calling the kettle black.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
imply that the accusers are being hypocritical.  To prove such a claim, you should offer specific incidents where this is the case along with using these points.<br>
<br>
<br>
The point<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
- What goes around, comes around.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
implies that the accusers will meet some &quot;just reward&quot; for actions being committed, such as this airing of grievances.  It is considered to be a &quot;karmaic warning&quot; or a &quot;veiled threat&quot;, depending on context.<br>
<br>
<br>
And the point<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>
- Let he who is without sin cast the first stone. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
says that no one should air any grievances in an attempt to relieve the stress that is on our server.  I have never been in favor of &quot;stewing&quot; over things.  When issues arise, I believe it is far better to resolve the issues and move on rather than let them eat away at you and cause even more bad feelings to grow.  When you stew over something, you will continue to look for more things to be annoyed by, with greater scrutiny.<br>
<br>
[edit] had text that was accusatory of a group of people purposefully acting in ways to bother people.  I meant it to be that the ways in which they acted bothered people, not that they acted in those ways purposefully to bother people. <p><P>
